    <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
    <p>Tillerstead LLC collects only the information necessary to provide our services and communicate with you:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Contact information</strong> — name, email address, phone number, and project address when you request a quote or contact us.</li>
      <li><strong>Project details</strong> — scope descriptions, photos, and measurements you provide for estimating purposes.</li>
      <li><strong>Website usage data</strong> — anonymous analytics (page views, referral sources) collected via privacy-respecting tools. No cross-site tracking.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
    <p>We use collected information solely to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Respond to inquiries and provide project estimates</li>
      <li>Coordinate scheduled work and communications</li>
      <li>Improve our website and services</li>
    </ul>
    <p>We do not sell, rent, or share your personal information with third parties for marketing purposes.</p>

    <h2>3. Data Security</h2>
    <p>We implement reasonable technical and organizational measures to protect your information. Project photos and documents are stored securely and retained only as long as necessary for project completion and warranty support.</p>

    <h2>4. Cookies &amp; Tracking</h2>
    <p>Our website uses minimal, functional cookies required for site operation. We do not use advertising trackers or third-party analytics cookies. Any analytics collected are aggregated and anonymized.</p>

    <h2>5. Third-Party Services</h2>
    <p>Our website may link to external resources (TCNA, ANSI standards references). We are not responsible for the privacy practices of external sites. We encourage reviewing their policies independently.</p>

    <h2>6. Your Rights</h2>
    <p>You may request access to, correction of, or deletion of your personal information at any time by contacting us at <a href="mailto:legal@tillerstead.com" style="color: var(--color-brand-primary);" class="hover:underline">legal@tillerstead.com</a>.</p>

    <h2>7. New Jersey Consumer Rights</h2>
    <p>Under the New Jersey Consumer Fraud Act and applicable state regulations, you have the right to transparent business practices. Tillerstead LLC operates under NJ Home Improvement Contractor license #13VH10808800.</p>

    <h2>8. Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <p>We may update this policy periodically. Changes will be posted on this page with a revised "Last updated" date. Continued use of our services constitutes acceptance of any changes.</p>

